        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 1:06AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 102 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking cluster strong
thunderstorms over central Crockett County, west and south of Ozona,
moving north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163, The Intersection Of Ranch
Road 2083 And Highway 405, The Intersection Of Highway 163 And Ranch
Road 1973, Ozona, Barnhart, I-10 Near The Crockett-
Sutton County Line, Us-190 Near The Crockett-
Sutton County Line, Ft Lancaster, The Intersection Of I-
10 And Highway 405, and The Intersection Of I-10 And Highway 290.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 334 and 380.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
